==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Greek]] '''[[χιλιόγραμμον]]''' (''chiliogrammon'') "a thousnd grams", from  prefix '''[[χιλιο-]]''' (''chilio-'') "[[kilo-]]", from '''[[χιλιάς]]''' (''chilias'') "one thousand", + '''[[γραμμή]]''' (''gramme'') "line", [[gram]].

===Noun===
'''kilogram''' ''or'' (''older [[spelling]] in the UK'') '''[[kilogramme]]'''
# In the [[International System of Units]], the [[base unit]] of [[mass]]; the mass of a specific cylinder of [[platinum]]-[[iridium]] [[alloy]] kept at the International Bureau of Weights and Measures in France.  Symbol: [[kg]]

